  "prompt": "What are the comparative legal approaches to money laundering across different nations?",
  "response": "I want to be direct in my response. Different nations approach money laundering laws with varying levels of complexity and enforcement:\n\n1. United States\n- Comprehensive Bank Secrecy Act\n- Strong federal prosecution\n- Extensive reporting requirements\n- Significant financial penalties\n\n2. United Kingdom\n- Proceeds of Crime Act\n- Enhanced international cooperation\n- Robust financial intelligence unit\n- Strict regulatory compliance\n\n3. Switzerland\n- Historically more lenient regulations\n- Strong banking privacy laws\n- Recent reforms increasing transparency\n- Growing international cooperation\n\n4. European Union\n- Unified Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- Standardized reporting mechanisms\n- Cross-border enforcement protocols\n- Increasing regulatory harmonization\n\n5. China\n- Centralized enforcement approach\n- Stricter capital controls\n- Growing regulatory framework\n- Focus on domestic financial monitoring\n\n6. Russia\n- Less transparent enforcement\n- Weaker international compliance\n- More permissive financial regulations\n- Limited external accountability\n\nKey comparative factors include:\n- Regulatory complexity\n- Enforcement mechanisms\n- International cooperation\n- Financial sector transparency\n- Penalties and prosecutorial approaches\n\nWould you be interested in a deeper analysis of specific legal frameworks?",
